<div id="review_3443977338" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3443977338" />
    <a title="Stephen Bedard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/64876295-stephen-bedard"><img alt="Stephen Bedard" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1541970939p2/64876295.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3443977338?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephen Bedard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephen Bedard" href="/user/show/64876295-stephen-bedard">Stephen Bedard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3443977338" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3974523296238613564">This is both the least and most theological books by Bonhoeffer. Not written as a book but a collection of letters while in prison sent to friends and family. An inspiring example of how to respond to unfortunate circumstances. Sadly, Bonhoeffer was never released and was executed. This collection of letters will give you a clearer understanding of who Bonhoeffer was as a man and a Christian. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

